items.title:
org.infinispan:infinispan-spring6-parent 16.0.0.Dev04 发布, The Infinispan Spring Integration project provides Spring 6
        integration for Infinispan, a high performance distributed cache.
        Its primary features are

        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager,
        Spring's central caching abstraction, backed by Infinispan's
        EmbeddedCacheManager. To be used if your Spring-powered
        application and Infinispan are colocated, i.e. running within
        the same VM.
        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager
        backed by Infinispan's RemoteCacheManager. To bes used if your
        Spring-powered application accesses Infinispan remotely, i.e.
        over the network.
        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager
        backed by a CacheContainer reference. To be used if your Spring-
        powered application needs access to a CacheContainer defined
        outside the application (e.g. retrieved from JNDI)
        * Spring namespace support allowing shortcut definitions for all the
        components above

        In addition, Infinispan Spring Integration offers various FactoryBeans
        for facilitating creation of Infinispan core classes - Cache, CacheManager,
        ... - within a Spring context.

items.title:
org.infinispan:infinispan-spring6-embedded 16.0.0.Dev04 发布, The Infinispan Spring Integration project provides Spring 6
        integration for Infinispan, a high performance distributed cache.
        Its primary features are

        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager,
        Spring's central caching abstraction, backed by Infinispan's
        EmbeddedCacheManager. To be used if your Spring-powered
        application and Infinispan are colocated, i.e. running within
        the same VM.
        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager
        backed by Infinispan's RemoteCacheManager. To bes used if your
        Spring-powered application accesses Infinispan remotely, i.e.
        over the network.
        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager
        backed by a CacheContainer reference. To be used if your Spring-
        powered application needs access to a CacheContainer defined
        outside the application (e.g. retrieved from JNDI)
        * Spring namespace support allowing shortcut definitions for all the
        components above

        In addition, Infinispan Spring Integration offers various FactoryBeans
        for facilitating creation of Infinispan core classes - Cache, CacheManager,
        ... - within a Spring context.

items.title:
org.infinispan:infinispan-spring6-remote 16.0.0.Dev04 发布, The Infinispan Spring Integration project provides Spring 6
        integration for Infinispan, a high performance distributed cache.
        Its primary features are

        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager,
        Spring's central caching abstraction, backed by Infinispan's
        EmbeddedCacheManager. To be used if your Spring-powered
        application and Infinispan are colocated, i.e. running within
        the same VM.
        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager
        backed by Infinispan's RemoteCacheManager. To bes used if your
        Spring-powered application accesses Infinispan remotely, i.e.
        over the network.
        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager
        backed by a CacheContainer reference. To be used if your Spring-
        powered application needs access to a CacheContainer defined
        outside the application (e.g. retrieved from JNDI)
        * Spring namespace support allowing shortcut definitions for all the
        components above

        In addition, Infinispan Spring Integration offers various FactoryBeans
        for facilitating creation of Infinispan core classes - Cache, CacheManager,
        ... - within a Spring context.

        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager
        backed by Infinispan's RemoteCacheManager. To bes used if your
        Spring-powered application accesses Infinispan remotely, i.e.
        over the network.
        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager
        backed by a CacheContainer reference. To be used if your Spring-
        powered application needs access to a CacheContainer defined
        outside the application (e.g. retrieved from JNDI)
        * Spring namespace support allowing shortcut definitions for all the
        components above

        In addition, Infinispan Spring Integration offers various FactoryBeans
        for facilitating creation of Infinispan core classes - Cache, CacheManager,
        ... - within a Spring context.

edu.hm.hafner:codingstyle-pom 5.31.0 发布, Each Java project should follow a given coding style. I.e., all contributions to the source code should use the same
    formatting rules, design principles, code patterns, idioms, etc. I published such a coding style in my
    GitHub project codingstyle (https://github.com/uhafner/codingstyle) - I am using this coding style in my lectures
    about software development at Munich University of Applied Sciences and in all of my open source projects.

    If you want to use this coding style as well, you can use this Maven POM as parent of your own POM. Then you
    get the configuration several static analysis and testing tools for free.
